The EntityEmitter (7) type is used to apply sounds to an entity.


Often used for entities that produce sounds, such as vending machines, air con units and fans.

Fields:

Current name   Type      FileRef Official name       Description
--
Name           metahash          Name                EntityEmitter name.
Flags          flags             Flags               Flags
Unk01          metahash  dat54   Sound               Main sound.
Unk02          float             MaxDistance         Unknown
Unk03          float             BusinessHoursProb   Unknown
Unk04          float             EveningProb         Unknown
Unk05          float             NightProb           Unknown
Unk06          float             ConeInnerAngle      Unknown
Unk07          float             ConeOuterAngle      Unknown
Unk08          float             ConeMaxAtten        Unknown
Unk09          metahash          StopAfterLoudSound  Unknown //Unused
Unk10          integer           MaxPathDepth        Unknown
Unk11          float             BrokenHealth        Unknown

Example:

<Item type="EntityEmitter" ntOffset="27951">
 <Name>ee_can_machine</Name>
 <Flags value="0xAAAA9A2A" />
 <Unk01>appliances_can_machine</Unk01>
 <Unk02 value="30" />
 <Unk03 value="0.8" />
 <Unk04 value="0.8" />
 <Unk05 value="0.8" />
 <Unk06 value="0" />
 <Unk07 value="0" />
 <Unk08 value="0" />
 <Unk09 />
 <Unk10 value="2" />
 <Unk11 value="-1" />
</Item>